All five fixes applied. Here's exactly what was wrong and why each fix works:

  ---
  Root cause

  sqlc's PostgreSQL parser resolves column names by looking through CTEs to their underlying tables. When two CTEs both query the same
  table (e.g. forecast_entries or employee_actuals), any column that table owns is visible from both CTEs simultaneously in the outer
  query scope — and sqlc flags it as ambiguous, even if the column isn't referenced in the outer SELECT at all.

  The recursive CTE anchor/recursion alias mismatch is a separate but related issue: sqlc sees two different "providers" of a column when
  the anchor uses an unaliased table and the recursion uses an aliased one.

  ---
  Fix-by-fix

  ┌─────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┐
  │            Error            │          Query           │             What was wrong             │               Fix               │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
  │ actuals.sql:164             │                          │ Both prev/curr CTEs query              │ Added ea alias + ea. prefix in  │
  │ import_run_id               │ ActualsMoMDelta          │ employee_actuals without alias — sqlc  │ both CTEs                       │
  │                             │                          │ sees import_run_id from both           │                                 │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
  │                             │                          │ FULL OUTER JOIN … USING                │ Replaced USING with ON          │
  │ actuals.sql:164             │ Same                     │ (costcenter_id) causes sqlc to merge   │ curr.costcenter_id =            │
  │                             │                          │ columns and then re-scan the           │ prev.costcenter_id              │
  │                             │                          │ underlying table providers             │                                 │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
  │                             │                          │ Anchor uses unaliased costcenters;     │ Added cc alias to anchor,       │
  │ costcenters.sql:105 id      │ GetCostcenterDescendants │ recursion uses aliased costcenters c — │ prefixed all anchor columns     │
  │                             │                          │  two providers of id                   │ with cc.                        │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
  │                             │                          │ Both CTEs query forecast_entries       │ Added fe alias in both CTEs;    │
  │ forecast_entries.sql:267    │ DiffVersionsByCC         │ without alias; USING (costcenter_id)   │ replaced USING with ON          │
  │ version_id                  │                          │ amplifies the look-through             │ a.costcenter_id =               │
  │                             │                          │                                        │ b.costcenter_id                 │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
  │ forecast_entries.sql:321    │ DiffVersionsByEmployee   │ Same — both CTEs query                 │ Added fe alias + fe. prefix in  │
  │ version_id                  │                          │ forecast_entries without alias         │ both CTEs                       │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
  │ forecast_versions.sql:113   │                          │ Anchor uses unaliased                  │ Added fv alias to anchor,       │
  │ id                          │ GetVersionChain          │ forecast_versions; recursion uses      │ prefixed anchor columns with    │
  │                             │                          │ forecast_versions fv                   │ fv.                             │
  └─────────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────┘

  The ORDER BY costcenter_id at the end of the diff queries was also changed to ORDER BY COALESCE(a.costcenter_id, b.costcenter_id) since
  after replacing USING with ON, the merged column no longer exists and the bare name would itself be ambiguous.

