      348  -- ── Audit history ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

● ORDER BY subject_key was ambiguous for the same reason as before: sqlc sees subject_key coming from both version_a a and version_b b.
  The SELECT aliases COALESCE(a.subject_key, b.subject_key) AS subject_key, but sqlc resolves ORDER BY against the input columns before
  the output alias is applied, so it finds two candidates.

  The fix ORDER BY COALESCE(a.subject_key, b.subject_key) matches exactly what the SELECT already computes, so the generated Go struct
  field will still be SubjectKey string. No semantic change — same query plan.
  
